## Section 3: Rollback Procedure

<!--
Complete this section BEFORE deployment. A rollback procedure written
after something goes wrong is written under pressure with incomplete
information. Write it now.

The rollback trigger is NON-OPTIONAL. Every deployment must define
the observable signal that means "execute rollback now."
-->

### Rollback Trigger

**Observable signal:** [The specific, measurable condition that means "rollback now" —
  e.g., "Smoke test exits non-zero" or "Error rate > 0.5% for 2 consecutive minutes"]
**Who decides:** [Role — e.g., "Deployer" or "On-call engineer"]
**Time threshold:** [How long to observe before declaring failure —
  e.g., "Immediate on smoke test failure" or "5 minutes of sustained error rate"]

